ygData.msgSnippet: Percussion 100% (store-bought) Wind 100% (store-bought) String 80% (less than store-bought) Brass 80% (less than store-bought) Singing 80% (which nothing else
ygData.messageBody:
Percussion 100% (store-bought)
Wind 100% (store-bought)
String 80% (less than store-bought)
Brass 80% (less than store-bought)
Singing 80% (which nothing else does)

Keep your drum and lute with you, even though in many cases you will not
switch them out, but a lot of times you will find it necessary. bank
the rest. and Grats =)

Shada/Erisi

-----Original Message-----
From: Rebecca Small [mailto:rsmall@...]
Sent: Tuesday, July 03, 2001 6:01 AM
To: 'eqbards@yahoogroups.com'
Subject: [eqbards] Finally!


I'm finally done with my epic! I knew it would be soon as the Maestro
finally dropped a 7 string when we were in Hate last Saturday. That
meant of
course I would soon finish the epic and not need the lute. I do have a
question that I have not seen a clear answer on: is the epic as powerful
as
all our best instruments or stronger in string, lesser in percussion?
I'm
just trying to figure out what instruments I don't need to carry around
anymore.
